Bxb4 30. Rac1 Ba5 31. Bf3 Bc7 $36 {Grischuk,A (2711)-Karjakin,S (2732)/Odessa
rpd/2008/}) 15. b3 {Another critical position, in which the theory was formed
mainly by two important games from last year's World Championship. This time
White chooses a third (and possibly the most promising) option.} (15. Bg3 Qxd4
16. Rfd1 (16. Rad1 Qb6 17. b3 $5 cxb3 18. axb3 a6 19. Rd2 c5 20. Rd6 Qa5 21. e5
