Qxa3 32. Be5 Rf7 33. Bg6 Rb7 34. Bxg7 Rxg7 35. Rxe6 $18) 31. Qxb6 (31. Qd8+ $5
Qf8 32. Qxb6 {/\} e5 33. Qe3 $18 {was equally strong.}) 31... e5 32. Qd8+ Qf8
33. Qa5 e4 {Black's last chance. However, even in time trouble Grischuk winds
up his -> effectively.} 34. Bxe4 (34. Qxc3 $6 Rxf2 35. Be5 Qc5 (35... Bxe5 36.
Qxe5 Rxc2 37. Rf1 $18) 36. Bxg7 Rxc2+ 37. Bd4 Rxc3 $16 {would only prolong the
game.}) 34... Nxe4 35. Rxe4 a3 36. Re3 {Disarms Black's o^[%csl Ra3]} Qf7 37.
Qxa3 Qxc4 38. Qa5 $18 {Black did his best to survive the direct ->, but (apart
